Stock Buyback For New York Times Co. 
The New York Times Co. said Thursday that its board had authorized the
repurchase of up to $100 million of its class A common stock.
The stock repurchase program is the second in a year at the company.
Thursday, The Times Co. said it had spent all of the $150 million
authorized under a program announced on Oct. 21, 1993.
Under the board's latest authorization, purchases may be made from time
to time on the open market or through private transactions. The Times
said the repurchased shares would be used for the company's stock-based
employee benefit plans and for other corporate purposes.
The company's class A common shares closed Thursday at $22 each, down
37.5 cents, on the American Stock Exchange.
